         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>MSS/050 Main Static Converters for the Astute Boats (Submarines)</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>MSS/050</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="31151000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The delivery of spares, repairs, post design services and technical support for the Main Static Converter (MSC) systems fitted to the Astute and Vanguard class of submarines.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">4200000</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>United Kingdom.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Marine Systems Support Marine Electrical (“MSS” “ME”) team, part of the UK Ministry of Defence, intends to award a contract to Ultra Electronics PMES for the delivery of spares, repairs, post design services and technical support for the Main Static Converter (MSC) systems fitted to the Astute and Vanguard glass of submarines. The estimated contract value is 4 200 000 GBP for the entire duration of the contract which is 5 years plus an option for a further 2 years.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
                  <AC_CRITERIA>
                     <AC_CRITERION>Authority is seeking technical compliance and value for money. No Acceptable Price, No Offer of Contract.</AC_CRITERION>
                     <AC_WEIGHTING>100</AC_WEIGHTING>
                  </AC_CRITERIA>
               </DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
               <OPTIONS/>
               <OPTIONS_DESCR>
                  <P>Contract will be awarded for 5 years with option to extend for 2 years.</P>
               </OPTIONS_DESCR>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
               <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                  <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                     <D_TECHNICAL/>
                  </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>The Marine Systems Support Marine Electrical (“MSS” “ME”) team, part of the UK Ministry of Defence, intends to award a contract to Ultra Electronics PMES for the delivery of spares, repairs, post design services and technical support for the Main Static Converter (MSC) systems fitted to the Astute and Vanguard glass of submarines. The estimated contract value is 4 200 000 GBP for the entire duration of the contract which is 5 years plus an option for a further 2 years.</P>
                     <P>It is considered that this contract can be placed using the negotiated procedure without prior publication of a contact notice pursuant to Article 28(1)(e) of Directive 2009/81/EC (Regulation 16(1)(a)(ii) of the Defence and Security Public Contracts Regulations 2011) for technical reasons.</P>
                     <P>Ultra Electronics PMES is the Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) of the MSC and have been responsible for the design and manufacture of the Main Static Converter systems fitted to the Astute and Vanguard class of submarines. The MSC system is a critical system which provides a fixed, solid state power electronics alternative to traditional Motor Generator (MG) sets which convert the submarine main AC electrical supply into a DC supply that is used for battery charging and other services.</P>
                     <P>Only the OEM Ultra Electronics PMES can deliver this requirement because only Ultra Electronics PMES have access to the manufacturing diagrams and specifications required to ensure that all components related to the MSC system are tested and compliant with the rigorous safety criteria required for fitting to a Submarine, and all components and equipment can integrate seamlessly with the wider static conversion system. The Authority does not have rights to access the required information and documentation to enable any other economic operator to reverse engineer such components and equipment. In addition, only Ultra Electronics PMES have access to the systems specific technical and design information required to properly support the systems. The Authority does not hold or have rights to such information and could not provide it to another supplier. Accordingly, only Ultra Electronics PMES can provide the required technical assurance and ensure the safety of the system as a whole.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
            </DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
            <NO_CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
